The Congress of South African Trade Unions (Cosatu) canceled speeches at a May Day rally including an expected address by President Jacob Zuma after the crowd became rowdy and some members booed Zuma.Zuma and his entourage could be seen on live TV hastily leaving the podium and being whisked in a large motorcade from the event in the central city of Bloemfontein.Cosatu, a key political ally of the ruling ANC, last month called on Zuma to step down after his change of finance ministers triggered a credit rating downgrade to &#8220;junk&#8221;.-Reuters 